<div class=3D"container mb-3">
    <div class=3D"row p-3">
        <div class=3D"col-12 section-block p-3 p-md-5 mb-3">
            <h2 class=3D"text-center text-light fw-semibold mb-3">What is A=
PM Test </h2>
            <p class=3D"mb-0">The acronym APM here stands for Actions Per M=
inute. Thus, the APM test is a
                response recording test. It records your reactions within a=
 specified time frame. Ultimately, it
                calculates the actions performed by you while playing withi=
n a minute. The reaction time is very
                important while playing action games. The lesser the reacti=
on time and the more the actions in less
                time, the better a gamer you are.</p>
        </div>
        <div class=3D"col-12 section-block p-3 p-md-5 mb-3">
            <h2 class=3D"text-center text-light fw-semibold mb-3">High and =
Low Action Per Minute </h2>
            <p class=3D"mb-0">As the name suggests, high and low actions pe=
r minute depict the numbers. High
                APM means more actions are performed within a minute. Where=
as, low APM denotes that, fewer actions are
                performed by the user per minute. A player with a high APM =
is a good gamer or a professional player.
                While the player with low APM is a beginner. You can calcul=
ate whether you have a low or high APM, using
                the APM test.</p>
        </div>
        <div class=3D"col-12 section-block p-3 p-md-5 mb-3">
            <h2 class=3D"text-center text-light fw-semibold mb-3">How is it=
 Calculated? </h2>
            <p class=3D"mb-0">When you take the <a href=3D"https://clickspe=
edtest.io/apm-test">APM test</a>, your accurate
                clicks are recorded in
                that specified time. Similarly, your inaccurate clicks are =
also calculated based on the target clicking.
                The number of times you clicked your target correctly is yo=
ur APM score. There are different difficulty
                levels to choose from before you take the APM test. Make su=
re you play the comfortable one, i.e., the
                one test which is moderate/ easy for you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class=3D"col-12 section-block p-3 p-md-5 mb-3">
            <h2 class=3D"text-center text-light fw-semibold mb-3">Why APM i=
s Important in Games? </h2>
            <p class=3D"mb-0">Your actions determine your win or loss in a =
game. In action play games, having
                more APM will help you perform better in that game. However=
, in a defensive game or any camouflage game,
                the lower the APM, the better. You need to perform your act=
ions wisely and decide when to have more or
                less APM in the game. Then and only then, you will stay on =
track in the game.</p>
        </div>
